WEBVTT

00:01.804 --> 00:03.006
MAN:
What are we drinking to?

00:03.006 --> 00:05.912
Mm, we should drink to me.

00:05.912 --> 00:08.851
Yeah, 'cause I just finished
a year's probation,

00:08.851 --> 00:10.822
and my ex-best friend
finally saw the light

00:10.822 --> 00:12.993
and invited me
to her stupid wedding.

00:12.993 --> 00:14.830
And, uh... Oh, yeah.

00:14.830 --> 00:17.101
I got, uh, my one-year chip.

00:18.169 --> 00:20.007
Mmm.

00:20.007 --> 00:22.011
♪ ♪

00:23.781 --> 00:26.019
-What are you looking at?
-Eighth grade.

00:26.019 --> 00:27.722
That was such
a tough year for you.

00:27.722 --> 00:29.726
Yeah, well, the bangs.

00:29.726 --> 00:32.498
Yeah, well, they are
violently irregular.

00:32.498 --> 00:34.536
-I looked like a troll.
-I know.

00:34.536 --> 00:37.308
Kids can be
so appropriately cruel.

00:38.343 --> 00:41.049
-I got this.
-No, no, no, come on, man.

00:41.049 --> 00:43.219
Well, it's not like
I don't owe you, okay?

00:43.219 --> 00:46.694
I left you high and dry
when I...

00:46.694 --> 00:48.063
kicked the bucket.

00:48.063 --> 00:51.102
One could argue
that I left you high and dry

00:51.102 --> 00:52.438
in the weeks and months
leading up to

00:52.438 --> 00:54.743
you kicking said bucket.

00:54.743 --> 00:56.647
Uh, years, actually.

00:56.647 --> 00:58.116
Was it years?

00:58.116 --> 00:59.653
It was years.

01:01.824 --> 01:03.326
Dad?

01:03.326 --> 01:04.696
I'm here.

01:05.732 --> 01:07.769
I can't see your face.

01:07.769 --> 01:09.973
Well, maybe you ought to watch
what you're drinking.

01:09.973 --> 01:12.011
Oh, shit.
I'm drinking.

01:13.313 --> 01:15.384
-But I really want to see you.
-You can't.

01:15.384 --> 01:18.323
This is a classic
alcoholic anxiety dream.

01:18.323 --> 01:21.897
I quit smoking 20 years ago
and I still dream about it.

01:21.897 --> 01:25.638
The good news is this means
that things are going well.

01:25.638 --> 01:28.410
Of course, the bad news
is that I'm still dead.

01:29.445 --> 01:32.451
Hey, don't let your mom
date anyone. Okay?

01:32.451 --> 01:34.121
I mean, uh, you know,
unless it's, like,

01:34.121 --> 01:36.627
Pierce Brosnan.
That I would get.

01:36.627 --> 01:39.265
You know.
The guy's a smoke show.

01:39.265 --> 01:41.904
She doesn't stand a chance
in hell with Pierce Brosnan.

01:41.904 --> 01:43.708
-I think that's why I chose him.
-Yeah.

01:43.708 --> 01:45.645
Don't let her date
Pierce Brosnan,

01:45.645 --> 01:46.914
-I changed my mind.
-Okay,

01:46.914 --> 01:48.149
-I'll let her know.
-Okay.

01:49.485 --> 01:50.955
Wait, Dad.

01:50.955 --> 01:53.059
♪ ♪

01:58.002 --> 02:00.006
(gasps)

02:11.195 --> 02:13.667
♪ ♪

02:27.027 --> 02:29.298
Okay.

02:29.298 --> 02:30.935
Sign here.

02:34.074 --> 02:35.645
Great.
Got it.

02:35.645 --> 02:38.416
Thank you.
Have a good life.

02:38.416 --> 02:41.122
That's it?
What's the next step?

02:41.122 --> 02:42.759
Nothing.
You turned in

02:42.759 --> 02:44.261
all your program attendance,
you paid your fines,

02:44.261 --> 02:46.065
you even completed
your community service.

02:46.065 --> 02:47.902
You were two hours over.

02:47.902 --> 02:49.673
-Oh. Is there,
-Good for you.

02:49.673 --> 02:51.743
-like, extra credit?
-No.

02:51.743 --> 02:54.950
The state of Massachusetts
doesn't offer extra credit.

02:54.950 --> 02:57.454
Right.
All right, so I'll, uh,

02:57.454 --> 02:59.358
check in with you
every month now?

02:59.358 --> 03:02.665
You check in with me never.
You're done.

03:02.665 --> 03:04.335
-Congratulations.
-(claps)

03:04.335 --> 03:06.105
Go revel in your freedom.
(whoops softly)

03:06.105 --> 03:07.407
Sure you don't want me to, like,

03:07.407 --> 03:09.278
pee in a cup,
for old time's sake?

03:09.278 --> 03:11.015
What is happening?

03:11.015 --> 03:13.921
-Do you enjoy
probation, Samantha?
-No.

03:13.921 --> 03:16.292
No, it's just weird. I've seen
you every week for, like,

03:16.292 --> 03:17.695
however many weeks
are in a year.

03:17.695 --> 03:21.235
52.
Weeks, yeah.

03:21.235 --> 03:24.809
I think I'm... gonna miss you.

03:24.809 --> 03:27.715
Well, tell you what,

03:27.715 --> 03:29.920
if you are desperate to see me,

03:29.920 --> 03:32.157
I will be at
your mom's book club.

03:32.157 --> 03:33.493
It's a trial period.

03:33.493 --> 03:34.896
And they are on trial.

03:34.896 --> 03:36.900
♪ ♪

03:37.635 --> 03:38.938
