practice. Just say what you mean

05:41.168 --> 05:43.673
-once-- nothing is worth
a paragraph. Nothing.
-No, I know, it's just...

05:43.673 --> 05:45.176
it's weird, you know?
He's really

05:45.176 --> 05:46.913
not the type to ghost, so...

05:46.913 --> 05:48.182
He'll make it or he won't.
Either way,

05:48.182 --> 05:49.284
there's a silver lining.

05:49.284 --> 05:50.854
-What's that?
-This is great for me.

05:50.854 --> 05:52.658
I actually still don't know
if I'm supposed to be here,

05:52.658 --> 05:54.294
so I'm gonna just cling to you
like a barnacle.

05:54.294 --> 05:56.532
What do you mean?
You said she invited you.

05:56.532 --> 05:58.703
Yes, technically, when she was
under the influence

05:58.703 --> 06:01.842
-of some pretty
gnarly stuff, so...
-Right.

06:01.842 --> 06:03.145
(car door closes)

06:03.145 --> 06:04.815
-FELICIA: Well, well,
-Okay.

06:04.815 --> 06:06.586
-Well.
-James.

06:06.586 --> 06:08.222
What nerve.
Hey, don't take him back.

06:08.222 --> 06:09.992
Actually, do what you want.
I don't care.

06:09.992 --> 06:11.963
-Hey, hey.
-Oh, my God, where were you?

06:11.963 --> 06:13.232
Oh, my God, I got rear-ended

06:13.232 --> 06:15.236
by some real piece of work,
and then

06:15.236 --> 06:16.606
I was waiting for insurance,

06:16.606 --> 06:18.208
the tow truck was late--
all kinds of stupid stuff.

06:18.208 --> 06:20.446
Oh, my God. Are you okay?
Did you get hurt?

06:20.446 --> 06:23.452
I-I'm fine, a little shook up.

06:23.452 --> 06:26.157
Too shook up to text?
Hi.

06:26.157 --> 06:28.128
I should have, but I was
just racing to get here,

06:28.128 --> 06:29.965
'cause I didn't want to miss...

06:29.965 --> 06:31.736
this, my God.

06:31.736 --> 06:34.975
Okay, well, I'm just
glad you're okay.

06:34.975 --> 06:36.979
